WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:08.443 --> 00:00:10.097
Previously on Bull...

2
00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:11.054
Ms. Rentzel?

3
00:00:11.098 --> 00:00:12.403
You recently met
a young woman

4
00:00:12.447 --> 00:00:13.622
by the name of Zola Macer.

5
00:00:13.665 --> 00:00:15.841
A hacker. goes by Tidal?

6
00:00:15.885 --> 00:00:17.582
You should be more careful
who you associate with.

7
00:00:17.626 --> 00:00:18.670
A new A.U.S.A.

8
00:00:18.714 --> 00:00:20.194
has been
assigned to Bull's case.

9
00:00:20.237 --> 00:00:21.804
Dr. Bull!

10
00:00:21.847 --> 00:00:23.110
Come on.
Finchy-doodle.

11
00:00:23.153 --> 00:00:24.807
- Parker Reilly.
- Well.

12
00:00:24.850 --> 00:00:26.200
if I'm gonna be wrongly
imprisoned for ten years.

13
00:00:26.243 --> 00:00:28.028
at least it's by the best.
The max is 15 years.

14
00:00:28.071 --> 00:00:29.420
and that's only
a sentencing guideline.

15
00:00:29.464 --> 00:00:30.552
I'd argue for more.

16
00:00:30.595 --> 00:00:31.683
You want to win this case.

17
00:00:31.727 --> 00:00:33.511
or do you want
to help

18
00:00:33.555 --> 00:00:35.035
get to the truth?

19
00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

20
00:00:52.226 --> 00:00:56.317
Looks like Babiack's
new supplier's a no-show.

21
00:00:56.360 --> 00:00:58.710
Okay. if there's
no deal. let's call it.

22
00:00:58.754 --> 00:01:00.582
- Try again tomorrow.
- Copy that.

23
00:01:00.625 --> 00:01:02.497
Before you go.
can you grab me a coffee?

24
00:01:02.540 --> 00:01:04.542
Cream and...

25
00:01:05.978 --> 00:01:07.328
...sugar.

26
00:01:07.371 --> 00:01:09.504
Scott. stay in place. You copy?

27
00:01:09.547 --> 00:01:12.463
Copy. Where am I looking?

28
00:01:12.507 --> 00:01:14.900
Front door.

29
00:01:21.429 --> 00:01:23.953
Danilo Kovalev.

30
00:01:23.996 --> 00:01:25.868
The agency's been trying
to bust Kovalev for decades.

31
00:01:36.357 --> 00:01:37.619
He's on the move.

32
00:01:37.662 --> 00:01:38.794
I'm gonna keep eyes on him.

33
00:01:38.837 --> 00:01:39.882
This could be our only chance.

34
00:01:39.925 --> 00:01:41.840
Wait for backup.

35
00:01:42.667 --> 00:01:45.801
You copy? Scott.

36
00:02:11.174 --> 00:02:13.220
You went behind

37
00:02:13.263 --> 00:02:15.526
Mr. Kovalev's back.

38
00:02:15.570 --> 00:02:17.920
I didn't do it.

39
00:02:17.963 --> 00:02:19.139
I wouldn't.

40
00:02:22.272 --> 00:02:24.231
Who were you meeting?

41
00:02:24.274 --> 00:02:26.972
No one. I swear.

42
00:02:37.287 --> 00:02:39.289
Nothing here.

43
00:02:39.333 --> 00:02:40.986
Lose it.

44
00:02:41.030 --> 00:02:42.945
Da.

45
00:02:54.261 --> 00:02:55.610
Hey!
So sorry.

46
00:02:55.653 --> 00:02:57.525
Watch it.

47
00:02:58.700 --> 00:03:00.005
Mr. Kovalev.

48
00:03:00.049 --> 00:03:01.355
On the house.

49
00:03:01.398 --> 00:03:02.486
Niko.

50
00:03:02.530 --> 00:03:03.966
You are very generous.

51
00:03:04.009 --> 00:03:05.446
Enjoy the pastry.

52
00:03:07.274 --> 00:03:09.145
I heard prison food sucks.

53
00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:10.973
Danilo Kovalev.

54
00:03:11.016 --> 00:03:12.322
You're under arrest.

55
00:03:12.366 --> 00:03:14.324
You have the right
to remain silent.

56
00:03:14.368 --> 00:03:15.586
Anything you say
can and will be...

57
00:03:17.632 --> 00:03:20.156
Oh. we bagged Kovalev.
Put that on my tombstone.

58
00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:22.114
For once. I'm actually looking
forward to the paperwork.

59
00:03:22.158 --> 00:03:23.420
Oh. I'll handle it.

60
00:03:23.464 --> 00:03:24.987
You got stuck logging
the evidence last time.

61
00:03:25.030 --> 00:03:26.815
I did. didn't I?

62
00:03:26.858 --> 00:03:29.296
Have at it. Hey. drinks tonight?

63
00:03:29.339 --> 00:03:30.775
Drinks tonight.

64
00:04:03.678 --> 00:04:05.593
Where are you?

65
00:04:06.420 --> 00:04:09.205
Well. you were supposed
to be here 20 minutes ago.

66
00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:11.947
And I'm not exaggerating when
I say a man's life is at stake.

67
00:04:11.990 --> 00:04:15.385
so-- No. no. no.
don't put me on hold.

68
00:04:17.169 --> 00:04:18.345
Oh. hi. there.

69
00:04:18.388 --> 00:04:20.999
- Are you in legal trouble?
- Finch!

70
00:04:21.043 --> 00:04:23.088
Finchy! Ah. Sit.

71
00:04:23.132 --> 00:04:25.047
Stay. Finchy.

72
00:04:25.090 --> 00:04:26.744
Get her. Yeah.

73
00:04:27.528 --> 00:04:29.791
No. I'm not
at the state-- Okay.

74
00:04:29.834 --> 00:04:33.098
No. I said federal courthouse.
not the state courthouse.

75
00:04:33.142 --> 00:04:36.014
No. not all courthouses
look the same.

76
00:04:36.058 --> 00:04:39.714
Give me a sec.
I'm a man in need of pepperoni.

77
00:04:39.757 --> 00:04:41.368
I know you can get the job done.

78
00:04:41.411 --> 00:04:42.804
Thank you.

79
00:04:42.847 --> 00:04:43.979
Hi. Reilly.

80
00:04:44.022 --> 00:04:45.197
You waiting for a pizza?

81
00:04:45.241 --> 00:04:46.895
I am waiting
for 30 pizzas. actually.

82
00:04:46.938 --> 00:04:49.637
What do you want with 30 pizzas?
A coronary?

83
00:04:49.680 --> 00:04:52.988
Well. I have 12 hungry jurors
about to deliberate.

84
00:04:53.031 --> 00:04:54.468
So I'm gonna place
those 30 pizzas

85
00:04:54.511 --> 00:04:56.208
right outside
the jury room door.

86
00:04:56.252 --> 00:04:58.341
Not inside.
'cause that would be bribery.
Oh...

87
00:04:58.385 --> 00:05:02.345
And I am going to. uh.
let the aroma waft into the room

88
00:05:02.389 --> 00:05:04.521
and they will come
to their decision more quickly.

89
00:05:04.565 --> 00:05:06.044
And the quicker the decision.

90
00:05:06.088 --> 00:05:08.177
the more likely
they are to acquit.

91
00:05:08.220 --> 00:05:09.352
Bingo.

92
00:05:09.396 --> 00:05:10.832
That doesn't break
any technical rules.

93
00:05:10.875 --> 00:05:12.355
but it is certainly unorthodox.

94
00:05:12.399 --> 00:05:13.835
Most good ideas are.

95
00:05:13.878 --> 00:05:16.664
Listen. I called TAC.
they told me I'd find you here.

96
00:05:16.707 --> 00:05:19.754
What crime am I being
falsely accused of now?

97
00:05:19.797 --> 00:05:22.322
No crime.
At least that I know of.

98
00:05:22.365 --> 00:05:25.368
Hmm.
I need your help.

99
00:05:25.412 --> 00:05:27.239
My help?

100
00:05:27.283 --> 00:05:28.719
Hmm.

101
00:05:28.763 --> 00:05:33.681
I'm prosecuting Danilo Kovalev
on a RICO murder charge.

102
00:05:33.724 --> 00:05:35.073
Yeah. I heard about that.

103
00:05:35.117 --> 00:05:37.206
Didn't a DEA agent see him
pull the trigger?

104
00:05:37.249 --> 00:05:39.339
Sounds like a slam dunk.
Yeah. not anymore.

105
00:05:39.382 --> 00:05:40.992
Tomorrow the DOJ's going public

106
00:05:41.036 --> 00:05:43.386
with the fact that
the DEA agent. Darren Scott.

107
00:05:43.430 --> 00:05:45.214
was caught stealing cash
from evidence.

108
00:05:45.257 --> 00:05:47.782
Now. he's refusing
to testify against Kovalev

109
00:05:47.825 --> 00:05:49.349
unless he gets immunity.

110
00:05:49.392 --> 00:05:51.046
Give him immunity.
if that's what it takes

111
00:05:51.089 --> 00:05:52.395
to lock up a drug lord.

112
00:05:52.439 --> 00:05:55.442
Scott stole from
the Kovalev arrest. too.

113
00:05:55.485 --> 00:06:00.229
Ah. and Kovalev's attorney
will use that to discredit him.

114
00:06:00.272 --> 00:06:02.100
Bingo.

115
00:06:02.144 --> 00:06:03.711
Well. it might hurt a bit.
but I still say

116
00:06:03.754 --> 00:06:06.061
the move here
is to put Scott on the stand.

117
00:06:06.104 --> 00:06:08.237
If I let Scott off the
hook. it sends the message

118
00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:09.804
that it's okay for
agents to be dirty.

119
00:06:09.847 --> 00:06:12.589
and dirty agents
compromise investigations.

120
00:06:12.633 --> 00:06:14.504
Which compromises prosecution.

121
00:06:14.548 --> 00:06:15.766
It's a domino effect.

122
00:06:15.810 --> 00:06:17.420
The entire
justice system suffers.

123
00:06:17.464 --> 00:06:19.379
So this slam dunk
is really more of a Hail Mary?

124
00:06:19.422 --> 00:06:21.381
Without Scott.

125
00:06:21.424 --> 00:06:23.078
I only have
circumstantial evidence.

126
00:06:23.121 --> 00:06:25.515
It'll be like prosecuting
with one arm behind my back.

127
00:06:25.559 --> 00:06:27.561
Yeah.
That's why...

128
00:06:27.604 --> 00:06:29.301
I want to hire you.

129
00:06:30.128 --> 00:06:31.303
No. you don't.

130
00:06:31.347 --> 00:06:32.087
I do.

131
00:06:32.130 --> 00:06:33.915
Really. you don't.

132
00:06:33.958 --> 00:06:36.004
Is this about our history?

133
00:06:36.047 --> 00:06:37.266
No. I have only
the fondest memory

134
00:06:37.309 --> 00:06:39.050
of you trying
to put me in prison.

135
00:06:39.094 --> 00:06:40.748
I know you were
just doing your job

136
00:06:40.791 --> 00:06:42.140
and I get that. but...

137
00:06:42.184 --> 00:06:44.142
All right. so what is it?

138
00:06:45.622 --> 00:06:47.407
I don't think
you'd like my process.

139
00:06:47.450 --> 00:06:48.843
You think outside the box.

140
00:06:48.886 --> 00:06:50.584
There's nothing wrong with that.

141
00:06:50.627 --> 00:06:52.063
How should I put this?

142
00:06:52.107 --> 00:06:56.938
I'm pepperoni pizza.
and you're steamed broccoli.

143
00:06:56.981 --> 00:06:58.069
So what?

144
00:06:58.113 --> 00:07:00.071
Combined just right.

145
00:07:00.115 --> 00:07:01.856
those two can taste
awfully good together.

146
00:07:01.899 --> 00:07:03.640
Can they?

147
00:07:03.684 --> 00:07:07.035
Look. Kovalev's on trial
for murdering one man.

148
00:07:07.078 --> 00:07:10.212
We suspect that that he is
responsible for a dozen others.

149
00:07:10.255 --> 00:07:12.432
None of those victims'
families got justice.

150
00:07:12.475 --> 00:07:16.261
This is the DOJ's one chance
to put Kovalev away for good.

151
00:07:16.305 --> 00:07:19.569
I need the best.
and-and-and you are the best.

152
00:07:21.179 --> 00:07:22.920
You should have led with that.

153
00:07:22.964 --> 00:07:25.009
You'll do it?
Well...

154
00:07:25.053 --> 00:07:26.881
I mean...

155
00:07:26.924 --> 00:07:28.099
What the hell?

156
00:07:28.143 --> 00:07:29.623
But when you find yourself
hating me

157
00:07:29.666 --> 00:07:31.755
and every move I make.
remember that I warned you.

158
00:07:31.799 --> 00:07:33.148
Noted. Thank you.

159
00:07:33.191 --> 00:07:35.498
Ooh. My acquittal is here.

160
00:07:35.542 --> 00:07:37.500
You want a slice?
Mm. mm-mm.

161
00:07:37.544 --> 00:07:38.458
Okay.

162
00:07:38.501 --> 00:07:40.547
Hey. guys. Thanks for coming.

163
00:07:40.590 --> 00:07:42.766
You finally made it.
We're going into the courthouse.

164
00:07:42.810 --> 00:07:45.769
Outside the jury deliberation
room. not inside.

165
00:07:45.813 --> 00:07:47.641
Come on. Double-time.

166
00:07:47.684 --> 00:07:48.729
I'll do this one.

167
00:07:49.730 --> 00:07:50.992
Okay.

168
00:07:51.732 --> 00:07:53.995
♪

169
00:08:00.697 --> 00:08:01.785
So. we're teaming up
with the man

170
00:08:01.829 --> 00:08:03.874
who tried to put Bull in prison?
Awkward.

171
00:08:03.918 --> 00:08:05.920
If Bull can get past that.
so can we.

172
00:08:05.963 --> 00:08:07.661
He did have his
back in the end.

173
00:08:07.704 --> 00:08:11.186
Okay. United States
v. Danilo Kovalev.

174
00:08:11.229 --> 00:08:13.014
Surprisingly. the first time
his name's been on the docket.

175
00:08:13.057 --> 00:08:14.145
Really?

176
00:08:14.189 --> 00:08:16.104
Guy's notorious.

177
00:08:16.147 --> 00:08:18.149
Notoriously hard to prosecute.

178
00:08:18.193 --> 00:08:19.760
I heard you guys aren't using
Agent Scott's testimony.

179
00:08:19.803 --> 00:08:21.588
- What about the partner?
- Agent Cooke

180
00:08:21.631 --> 00:08:24.416
was in the van. so she was
not a witness to the shooting.

181
00:08:24.460 --> 00:08:26.244
And she didn't see Kovalev

182
00:08:26.288 --> 00:08:29.247
enter or exit the basement
where the murder took place.

183
00:08:29.291 --> 00:08:30.466
Surely someone
from the coffee shop

184
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.381
could place Kovalev
in the basement.

185
00:08:32.424 --> 00:08:34.644
Probably.
but Kovalev's reputation

186
00:08:34.688 --> 00:08:37.908
as a dangerous crime boss
is keeping people quiet.

187
00:08:37.952 --> 00:08:39.170
All except one.

188
00:08:39.214 --> 00:08:41.216
Francesca Gant.

189
00:08:41.259 --> 00:08:42.783
A customer. We're
prepping her today.

190
00:08:42.826 --> 00:08:44.480
Yeah. I'm sorry.

191
00:08:44.524 --> 00:08:47.135
but one witness placing Kovalev
near but not at the crime scene?

192
00:08:47.178 --> 00:08:48.615
If I'm defense counsel.

193
00:08:48.658 --> 00:08:50.791
I'm ripping that apart.
Admittedly.

194
00:08:50.834 --> 00:08:52.488
the evidence is thin.
but Kovalev

195
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:55.012
had someone with him
that day. an associate.

196
00:08:55.056 --> 00:08:57.232
We find him and
we flip him.

197
00:08:57.275 --> 00:08:59.626
Uh. we only have
a first name. Olek.

198
00:08:59.669 --> 00:09:00.931
But the. uh.

199
00:09:00.975 --> 00:09:02.933
DEA suspects
he fled to Warsaw.

200
00:09:02.977 --> 00:09:04.979
We have agents
on the ground there now.

201
00:09:05.022 --> 00:09:06.458
Taylor.

202
00:09:06.502 --> 00:09:08.112
you are gonna coordinate
with the DEA search.

203
00:09:08.156 --> 00:09:11.768
On it.
Actually.
you're off it.

204
00:09:11.812 --> 00:09:13.117
Excuse me?

205
00:09:13.161 --> 00:09:15.163
Ms. Rentzel didn't
pass DOJ clearance.

206
00:09:15.206 --> 00:09:16.338
What are you
talking about?

207
00:09:16.381 --> 00:09:17.600
She's one of the most
skilled analysts

208
00:09:17.644 --> 00:09:19.036
in her field.
I understand that.

209
00:09:19.080 --> 00:09:20.168
but her association

210
00:09:20.211 --> 00:09:21.604
with a hacker named Tidal

211
00:09:21.648 --> 00:09:23.867
earlier this year
caused some internal concerns.

212
00:09:23.911 --> 00:09:25.173
What are you
talking about?

213
00:09:25.216 --> 00:09:26.783
She was cleared
of any wrongdoing.

214
00:09:26.827 --> 00:09:28.568
It doesn't matter. Even the
suggestion of Ms. Rentzel's

215
00:09:28.611 --> 00:09:31.266
criminal association could
taint the investigation.

216
00:09:31.309 --> 00:09:33.398
So not only are our hands
tied behind our back.

217
00:09:33.442 --> 00:09:34.922
but you're cutting
our head off. too?

218
00:09:34.965 --> 00:09:36.010
I'm not cutting off anything.

219
00:09:36.053 --> 00:09:37.489
We have a very capable DEA team

220
00:09:37.533 --> 00:09:39.622
already searching.
It's not my team.

221
00:09:39.666 --> 00:09:40.710
It's okay. Bull.

222
00:09:40.754 --> 00:09:41.885
I'm sure the DEA
can handle this.

223
00:09:41.929 --> 00:09:43.278
No. this is ridiculous.

224
00:09:43.321 --> 00:09:45.715
Really.
I'm good.

225
00:09:45.759 --> 00:09:48.239
Just drop it. please?

226
00:09:50.067 --> 00:09:51.199
Okay.

227
00:09:51.242 --> 00:09:54.245
Danny. you will be the liaison

228
00:09:54.289 --> 00:09:55.246
with the DEA search.

229
00:09:55.290 --> 00:09:58.815
and that is nonnegotiable.

230
00:09:58.859 --> 00:10:00.948
Not a problem.

231
00:10:00.991 --> 00:10:02.863
You see? We found a compromise.

232
00:10:02.906 --> 00:10:05.909
Broccoli and pizza.

233
00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:08.738
I was at the back
of the coffee shop

234
00:10:08.782 --> 00:10:10.348
near the staircase when this guy

235
00:10:10.392 --> 00:10:12.873
came out of nowhere
and bumped into me.

236
00:10:12.916 --> 00:10:15.571
And this was the defendant.
Danilo Kovalev?

237
00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:16.790
Yes.

238
00:10:16.833 --> 00:10:18.226
I remember because
when he bumped into me.

239
00:10:18.269 --> 00:10:20.097
my coffee went everywhere.

240
00:10:20.141 --> 00:10:21.403
Okay. hold on.
let's pause for a second.

241
00:10:21.446 --> 00:10:23.318
You said
he "bumped" into you.

242
00:10:23.361 --> 00:10:25.712
but maybe it was more of a push?

243
00:10:25.755 --> 00:10:28.497
I wouldn't really
describe it as a push.

244
00:10:28.540 --> 00:10:29.933
Ah. how would you describe it?

245
00:10:29.977 --> 00:10:31.587
As a bump.

246
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:33.328
Mm. Bump.

247
00:10:33.371 --> 00:10:35.896
Just looking for another word.

248
00:10:35.939 --> 00:10:37.724
Maybe "shove"?

249
00:10:37.767 --> 00:10:39.595
Sorry. it was just a bump.

250
00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:40.814
Okay. just...

251
00:10:40.857 --> 00:10:42.946
work with me here.
help me find a synonym.

252
00:10:42.990 --> 00:10:44.818
Maybe he collided with you?

253
00:10:44.861 --> 00:10:45.819
Bull?

254
00:10:45.862 --> 00:10:47.081
Can I speak with you?

255
00:10:47.124 --> 00:10:48.691
Sure.

256
00:10:52.477 --> 00:10:54.262
Don't put words
into my witness's mouth.

257
00:10:54.305 --> 00:10:57.134
Oh. I thought she
was our witness.

258
00:10:57.178 --> 00:10:58.570
A pizza gag is one thing.

259
00:10:58.614 --> 00:11:00.355
but lying is a boundary
I will not cross.

260
00:11:00.398 --> 00:11:01.922
Okay. I don't
want her to lie.

261
00:11:01.965 --> 00:11:06.578
but right now. her testimony.
it's limited.

262
00:11:09.146 --> 00:11:11.583
Look. she didn't see
Kovalev pull the trigger.

263
00:11:11.627 --> 00:11:13.673
She didn't even see a gun.

264
00:11:15.457 --> 00:11:17.677
I need to tell a story.

265
00:11:17.720 --> 00:11:19.243
Yeah. but you're trying
to change her story

266
00:11:19.287 --> 00:11:21.593
before she's finished
telling it.
No.

267
00:11:21.637 --> 00:11:22.986
"Bumped" is a friendly word.

268
00:11:23.030 --> 00:11:25.772
We need to paint Kovalev
as a stone-cold killer.

269
00:11:25.815 --> 00:11:28.862
Killers don't bump.
She needs oomph.

270
00:11:28.905 --> 00:11:31.255
I want facts. not oomph.
Okay.

271
00:11:31.299 --> 00:11:32.822
So you want
to put Kovalev in prison.

272
00:11:32.866 --> 00:11:34.258
you've hired me
to help you do that.

273
00:11:34.302 --> 00:11:37.044
and I'm telling you
that this word "bump"

274
00:11:37.087 --> 00:11:39.046
is not gonna convince 12 jurors

275
00:11:39.089 --> 00:11:41.570
to put someone away
for the rest of their life.

276
00:11:41.613 --> 00:11:45.661
I mean. if you want
to give it a try. go for it.

277
00:11:46.706 --> 00:11:48.664
Okay.

278
00:11:49.534 --> 00:11:51.798
Uh. let's. uh. try this again.

279
00:11:51.841 --> 00:11:53.277
This time with

280
00:11:53.321 --> 00:11:56.716
a little more... oomph.

281
00:12:00.676 --> 00:12:03.461
So. I checked in with the DEA
team that's hunting Olek.

282
00:12:03.505 --> 00:12:05.463
They've been searching
the same Warsaw spots for weeks

283
00:12:05.507 --> 00:12:06.856
and coming up empty.

284
00:12:06.900 --> 00:12:09.641
It's like a depressing game
of Where's Waldo?

285
00:12:09.685 --> 00:12:10.991
We need you.

286
00:12:11.034 --> 00:12:13.384
Love to be able to
help. but I'm benched.

287
00:12:13.428 --> 00:12:14.777
You're just gonna accept that?

288
00:12:14.821 --> 00:12:16.213
I don't want to taint
the investigation.

289
00:12:16.257 --> 00:12:19.434
Come on.
you're not gonna taint anything.

290
00:12:19.477 --> 00:12:21.958
I put a lot in jeopardy
when I worked with Tidal.

291
00:12:22.002 --> 00:12:24.004
I don't want
to jeopardize this case. too.

292
00:12:24.831 --> 00:12:26.093
Did you know this Olek guy

293
00:12:26.136 --> 00:12:28.269
is suspected of killing
multiple people?

294
00:12:28.312 --> 00:12:32.186
I thought Kovalev was
the shooter.
This time.

295
00:12:32.229 --> 00:12:35.015
But rumor is. Olek's got
a pretty big body count himself.

296
00:12:35.058 --> 00:12:36.581
He needs to be
taken off the streets.

297
00:12:36.625 --> 00:12:38.409
So now you're guilt-tripping me.

298
00:12:38.453 --> 00:12:40.411
Yes.
The answer's still no.

299
00:12:41.935 --> 00:12:44.502
Can you just reach out
to your contacts at Homeland?

300
00:12:44.546 --> 00:12:45.982
See if they can
point the DEA

301
00:12:46.026 --> 00:12:47.462
in the right direction overseas?

302
00:12:47.505 --> 00:12:49.725
I'm sure the DEA's
checked in with Homeland.

303
00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:51.814
Government agencies rarely know
what the other hand is doing.

304
00:12:51.858 --> 00:12:53.642
They're too proud
and territorial.

305
00:12:53.685 --> 00:12:55.165
True.

306
00:12:55.209 --> 00:12:57.515
Look. I'll keep your involvement
off the books.

307
00:12:57.559 --> 00:12:58.821
Just a call to Homeland.

308
00:12:58.865 --> 00:13:00.910
That's all I'm asking.

309
00:13:02.129 --> 00:13:06.176
Furthermore. the evidence
will show that Danilo Kovalev

310
00:13:06.220 --> 00:13:08.831
was in the coffee shop's
basement that morning.

311
00:13:10.224 --> 00:13:13.880
My question to you. the jury.
is simple: why else

312
00:13:13.923 --> 00:13:16.099
was Kovalev in that basement.

313
00:13:16.143 --> 00:13:18.710
other than to murder
Konstantin Ba...

314
00:13:20.843 --> 00:13:22.889
Whosever phone that is.
turn it off.

315
00:13:22.932 --> 00:13:25.326
before I have court security
confiscate it.

316
00:13:25.369 --> 00:13:27.023
Your Honor. excuse me.

317
00:13:27.067 --> 00:13:29.939
It is my mother's
medication reminder.

318
00:13:29.983 --> 00:13:31.680
May I quickly help her?

319
00:13:31.723 --> 00:13:34.596
Very well. but please hurry.

320
00:13:34.639 --> 00:13:36.119
Yes.

321
00:13:37.599 --> 00:13:39.383
Mamochka.

322
00:13:39.427 --> 00:13:41.821
It's okay. I got it.

323
00:13:47.087 --> 00:13:49.219
Forget "not guilty."
this guy wants an Oscar.

324
00:13:49.263 --> 00:13:50.873
I don't know
what Kovalev's doing.

325
00:13:50.917 --> 00:13:52.832
but I just lost two jurors.

326
00:13:52.875 --> 00:13:54.572
I apologize
for the interruption.

327
00:13:54.616 --> 00:13:56.226
Mr. Reilly. please continue.

328
00:13:56.270 --> 00:13:57.837
I was essentially done.
Your Honor.

329
00:13:57.880 --> 00:13:59.926
Since Ms. Lamont's
reserving her opening.

330
00:13:59.969 --> 00:14:02.015
are you ready to proceed
with your first witness?

331
00:14:02.058 --> 00:14:03.930
Yes. the government
would like to...

332
00:14:03.973 --> 00:14:05.279
One moment. Your Honor.

333
00:14:05.322 --> 00:14:07.107
What is it?
Ask for a recess.

334
00:14:07.150 --> 00:14:08.978
No. we need to keep
momentum with the jury.

335
00:14:09.022 --> 00:14:11.372
Ask for a recess
or I will throw this pencil

336
00:14:11.415 --> 00:14:13.156
at the judge and we will
get one the hard way.

337
00:14:13.200 --> 00:14:14.854
Very funny.

338
00:14:17.857 --> 00:14:20.381
The government requests
a brief recess.

339
00:14:21.251 --> 00:14:23.297
Kovalev put on quite
a show in there.

340
00:14:23.340 --> 00:14:25.168
I know. The good son act.
Hey. don't worry.

341
00:14:25.212 --> 00:14:26.648
I'm sure the jury
saw through it.

342
00:14:26.691 --> 00:14:28.215
I don't think so.

343
00:14:28.258 --> 00:14:29.999
You were busy watching Kovalev.
I was watching the jury.

344
00:14:30.043 --> 00:14:32.088
They wanted to hug
that cuddly bastard.

345
00:14:32.132 --> 00:14:33.133
Oh. come on.

346
00:14:33.176 --> 00:14:34.917
Kovalev is obviously
a sociopath.

347
00:14:34.961 --> 00:14:37.615
You can't get more dead
behind the eyes than that man.

348
00:14:37.659 --> 00:14:39.269
You see him that way because
you know about his crimes.

349
00:14:39.313 --> 00:14:42.272
You are primed
to see a sociopath.

350
00:14:42.316 --> 00:14:44.057
The jury comes in a blank slate.

351
00:14:44.100 --> 00:14:45.232
And now?

352
00:14:45.275 --> 00:14:46.842
And now. that slate reads
"angelic son."

353
00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:48.191
We need to convince them

354
00:14:48.235 --> 00:14:50.063
that he is
a dangerous criminal. Reilly.

355
00:14:50.106 --> 00:14:52.674
I just told them that
in my opening statement.

356
00:14:52.717 --> 00:14:54.937
We need to show them.
not tell them.

357
00:14:56.547 --> 00:14:58.941
If Kovalev is playing theater...

358
00:15:00.725 --> 00:15:03.337
...I think it's time
we went full opera.

359
00:15:04.251 --> 00:15:05.687
♪

360
00:15:07.602 --> 00:15:08.995
Objection.

361
00:15:09.038 --> 00:15:10.953
These theatrics are
outrageously prejudicial.

362
00:15:10.997 --> 00:15:13.608
Your Honor. the safety of our
witness is of paramount...

363
00:15:13.651 --> 00:15:14.957
All parties to the bench. now.

364
00:15:20.223 --> 00:15:22.704
This bodyguard stunt
is clearly intended

365
00:15:22.747 --> 00:15:24.314
to make my client
look dangerous

366
00:15:24.358 --> 00:15:25.663
in front of the jury.
He is dangerous.

367
00:15:25.707 --> 00:15:27.535
Dr. Bull. please.

368
00:15:27.578 --> 00:15:28.797
Using these marshals

369
00:15:28.840 --> 00:15:30.668
to paint the defendant
as violent

370
00:15:30.712 --> 00:15:33.497
is not only prejudicial.
it's disappointing.

371
00:15:33.541 --> 00:15:34.934
I expect better
from the government.

372
00:15:34.977 --> 00:15:36.370
I'm sorry. Your Honor.

373
00:15:36.413 --> 00:15:37.893
Marshals. you may be excused.

374
00:15:37.937 --> 00:15:39.329
Your presence here
is unnecessary.

375
00:15:39.373 --> 00:15:41.331
Now. let's get

376
00:15:41.375 --> 00:15:43.943
to the witness.
and no more antics.

377
00:15:43.986 --> 00:15:46.293
Got it?
Of course. Your Honor.

378
00:15:47.163 --> 00:15:49.209
I feel icky.
That was a cheap stunt.

379
00:15:49.252 --> 00:15:52.125
It was worth it. They're
scared of him now.

380
00:15:56.433 --> 00:15:57.565
Ms. Gant.

381
00:15:57.608 --> 00:15:58.958
where were you
around. uh. 10:00 a.m.

382
00:15:59.001 --> 00:16:00.655
on Wednesday.
February 9?

383
00:16:00.698 --> 00:16:04.050
I was at the Romanian Garden
coffee shop near Ocean Parkway.

384
00:16:04.093 --> 00:16:05.573
I like to study there sometimes.

385
00:16:05.616 --> 00:16:09.055
And did anything unusual
happen that morning

386
00:16:09.098 --> 00:16:10.186
of February 9?

387
00:16:10.230 --> 00:16:11.709
Not that I recall.

388
00:16:12.884 --> 00:16:15.365
You don't recall anything
out of the ordinary?

389
00:16:15.409 --> 00:16:16.714
No.

390
00:16:16.758 --> 00:16:18.934
Do you remember
spilling your coffee?

391
00:16:18.978 --> 00:16:20.370
Yes.

392
00:16:20.414 --> 00:16:23.634
Excellent. And do you recall
who spilled your coffee?

393
00:16:23.678 --> 00:16:25.027
No.

394
00:16:25.071 --> 00:16:25.985
Uh-oh.

395
00:16:26.028 --> 00:16:26.811
Did someone catch a case

396
00:16:26.855 --> 00:16:28.422
of witness amnesia?

397
00:16:28.465 --> 00:16:30.902
- Looks like it.
- You don't remember

398
00:16:30.946 --> 00:16:32.730
who collided with you

399
00:16:32.774 --> 00:16:35.037
and spilled coffee
all over your shirt?

400
00:16:35.081 --> 00:16:36.996
No.

401
00:16:38.432 --> 00:16:40.216
Your Honor.

402
00:16:40.260 --> 00:16:42.436
I'd like permission to treat
Ms. Gant as a hostile witness.

403
00:16:42.479 --> 00:16:44.046
Granted. You may proceed
with leading questions.

404
00:16:44.090 --> 00:16:46.396
Ms. Gant. isn't it true
that the person

405
00:16:46.440 --> 00:16:48.746
who spilled your coffee
was the defendant.

406
00:16:48.790 --> 00:16:49.921
Danilo Kovalev?

407
00:16:49.965 --> 00:16:51.793
I can't recall.And isn't it true

408
00:16:51.836 --> 00:16:53.490
that at the time Kovalev
spilled your coffee.

409
00:16:53.534 --> 00:16:56.363
he was coming from the staircase
that leads to the basement?

410
00:16:56.406 --> 00:16:58.278
I can't recall.
Ms. Gant.

411
00:16:58.321 --> 00:17:00.410
may I remind you
that the penalties of perjury

412
00:17:00.454 --> 00:17:02.064
include serious prison time?

413
00:17:02.108 --> 00:17:03.892
Now. I'll ask you
once more.

414
00:17:03.935 --> 00:17:07.069
didn't you see the defendant
come from the basement?

415
00:17:07.113 --> 00:17:08.288
The same basement

416
00:17:08.331 --> 00:17:09.941
where Konstantin BABIACK
was found murdered?

417
00:17:09.985 --> 00:17:11.943
Objection.
I'm allowed to ask
leading questions.

418
00:17:11.987 --> 00:17:13.945
But you're not allowed
to testify for her.

419
00:17:13.989 --> 00:17:14.946
I'm doing no such thing.
Your Honor.

420
00:17:14.990 --> 00:17:16.209
Overruled.

421
00:17:17.775 --> 00:17:19.081
Ms. Gant. please
answer the question.

422
00:17:19.125 --> 00:17:20.300
Did you see
the defendant

423
00:17:20.343 --> 00:17:21.692
come up from the basement?

424
00:17:21.736 --> 00:17:23.781
It doesn't matter
how many times you ask me.

425
00:17:23.825 --> 00:17:25.174
I can't remember.

426
00:17:29.222 --> 00:17:30.832
Kovalev got to Francesca.

427
00:17:30.875 --> 00:17:32.268
We've lost our witness.

428
00:17:32.312 --> 00:17:34.662
No. we've lost our case.

429
00:17:41.321 --> 00:17:43.062
All right.

430
00:17:43.105 --> 00:17:45.281
There's only one way to win now.
You know what we need to do.

431
00:17:45.325 --> 00:17:47.022
Yeah. I'll go back to the
witnesses from the coffee shop.

432
00:17:47.066 --> 00:17:48.328
See if I can get someone
to change their mind

433
00:17:48.371 --> 00:17:49.894
about testifying.

434
00:17:49.938 --> 00:17:51.592
So Kovalev can scare them
the way he scared Francesca?

435
00:17:51.635 --> 00:17:54.464
Fine. I'll put Agent Cooke
on the stand.

436
00:17:54.508 --> 00:17:56.379
She wasn't inside. Won't work.

437
00:17:56.423 --> 00:17:58.468
I'll call an expert witness.
Someone from the task force

438
00:17:58.512 --> 00:18:00.427
investigating
the Kovalev operation.

439
00:18:00.470 --> 00:18:01.776
Won't work.

440
00:18:01.819 --> 00:18:03.995
I know you don't like this.

441
00:18:04.039 --> 00:18:06.955
but there's only one witness
who can put Kovalev in prison.

442
00:18:11.525 --> 00:18:13.396
In exchange for your testimony.

443
00:18:13.440 --> 00:18:16.660
the government is willing to
reduce your current sentence

444
00:18:16.704 --> 00:18:19.359
from ten years to four.

445
00:18:19.402 --> 00:18:20.795
I thought you guys came to play.

446
00:18:20.838 --> 00:18:22.362
It's a decent deal.

447
00:18:22.405 --> 00:18:26.017
I want better than decent.
or you can find another witness.

448
00:18:29.238 --> 00:18:30.892
Fine. One year.

449
00:18:30.935 --> 00:18:32.502
That is as low
as I'll go.

450
00:18:32.546 --> 00:18:34.504
No. I want out today.

451
00:18:34.548 --> 00:18:35.810
A year is nothing.

452
00:18:35.853 --> 00:18:38.073
It'll pass in the blink
of an eye.

453
00:18:38.943 --> 00:18:41.337
I am not gonna make it a year.

454
00:18:41.381 --> 00:18:42.991
They're gonna kill me in here.

455
00:18:43.034 --> 00:18:44.297
You should have
thought of that

456
00:18:44.340 --> 00:18:45.559
before you broke the law.

457
00:18:45.602 --> 00:18:47.909
I kept the streets safe
for kids.

458
00:18:47.952 --> 00:18:49.824
I put criminals away.

459
00:18:49.867 --> 00:18:51.869
I put my life
on the line every day

460
00:18:51.913 --> 00:18:53.871
and barely made
more than minimum wage.

461
00:18:54.742 --> 00:18:56.526
I just took
what I deserved.

462
00:18:56.570 --> 00:18:58.615
You deserve prison time.

463
00:19:00.748 --> 00:19:04.491
Look. my dad has
advanced Alzheimer's.

464
00:19:04.534 --> 00:19:07.015
I couldn't take care
of him on my salary.

465
00:19:07.058 --> 00:19:10.192
The federal government doesn't
need that money. My dad did.

466
00:19:10.236 --> 00:19:11.846
What does it matter?

467
00:19:11.889 --> 00:19:14.936
It matters because you took
an oath. The same one I did.

468
00:19:14.979 --> 00:19:18.853
And if it's meaningless to one.
it's meaningless to all.

469
00:19:21.464 --> 00:19:23.074
Today.

470
00:19:27.949 --> 00:19:30.081
You're lucky there's someone
out there he wants to put away

471
00:19:30.125 --> 00:19:31.605
more than you.

472
00:19:36.827 --> 00:19:38.612
You owe me. Big-time.

473
00:19:38.655 --> 00:19:40.222
Why?

474
00:19:40.266 --> 00:19:43.225
My call to my Homeland contact
turned into a two-hour lunch.

475
00:19:43.269 --> 00:19:45.575
He kept on trying to sit
on my side of the booth

476
00:19:45.619 --> 00:19:47.098
for "security reasons."

477
00:19:47.142 --> 00:19:49.362
Wasn't fun.
Did you at least get

478
00:19:49.405 --> 00:19:50.928
anything out of it?
Yeah.

479
00:19:50.972 --> 00:19:52.930
He ran the Olek photo
through facial recognition.

480
00:19:52.974 --> 00:19:55.237
He hasn't boarded any flights
since the murder.

481
00:19:55.281 --> 00:19:56.760
He's not in Warsaw.

482
00:19:56.804 --> 00:19:57.674
Well. the DEA's looking
in the wrong direction.

483
00:19:57.718 --> 00:19:58.806
I got to text them.

484
00:19:58.849 --> 00:19:59.981
I just got word from Bull.

485
00:20:00.024 --> 00:20:01.330
Agent Scott is cooperating.

486
00:20:01.374 --> 00:20:02.940
Bull and Reilly
are prepping him tonight.

487
00:20:02.984 --> 00:20:05.116
We don't need Olek for trial?

488
00:20:05.160 --> 00:20:07.249
Oh. no. If we can find Olek.
we want him.

489
00:20:07.293 --> 00:20:08.685
Scott's an eyewitness.

490
00:20:08.729 --> 00:20:09.947
but he's also corrupt.

491
00:20:09.991 --> 00:20:10.948
The jury might not think
his word

492
00:20:10.992 --> 00:20:12.123
is enough to convict.

493
00:20:12.167 --> 00:20:13.560
Damn it.

494
00:20:13.603 --> 00:20:15.344
Well. the DEA's not gonna be
much use finding him.

495
00:20:15.388 --> 00:20:16.824
Why not?

496
00:20:16.867 --> 00:20:18.042
Taylor got a tip
from Homeland

497
00:20:18.086 --> 00:20:20.610
that Olek hasn't
left the country.

498
00:20:20.654 --> 00:20:22.960
I passed the intel on
to my DEA guy

499
00:20:23.004 --> 00:20:24.832
and all he said is.
"I'll look into it."

500
00:20:24.875 --> 00:20:25.963
You know what that means.

501
00:20:26.007 --> 00:20:27.226
"Don't call us. we'll call you."

502
00:20:27.269 --> 00:20:28.836
Yep. the bureaucratic
kiss-off.

503
00:20:28.879 --> 00:20:29.837
They're never gonna
find Olek if they keep

504
00:20:29.880 --> 00:20:31.099
dicking around Warsaw.

505
00:20:31.142 --> 00:20:32.187
Hold up.

506
00:20:32.231 --> 00:20:33.623
You've been helping

507
00:20:33.667 --> 00:20:35.016
with the search
for Olek?

508
00:20:35.886 --> 00:20:37.627
All I did was make a phone call.

509
00:20:37.671 --> 00:20:39.499
And eat too much green curry

510
00:20:39.542 --> 00:20:40.761
with an annoying
ex-colleague.

511
00:20:40.804 --> 00:20:41.979
But I'm back
on the bench.

512
00:20:42.023 --> 00:20:43.329
where I'm supposed to be.
No. no. no.

513
00:20:43.372 --> 00:20:44.373
I don't want you on the bench.

514
00:20:44.417 --> 00:20:45.809
You heard Danny.
The DEA

515
00:20:45.853 --> 00:20:47.768
is not gonna find Olek
on their own.

516
00:20:48.551 --> 00:20:49.639
Well.
you heard Reilly.

517
00:20:49.683 --> 00:20:50.945
If I'm involved

518
00:20:50.988 --> 00:20:52.425
in the investigation.
it could get tainted.

519
00:20:52.468 --> 00:20:54.165
Maybe. maybe not. Reilly
is not right about everything.

520
00:20:54.209 --> 00:20:55.689
He thought Bull was a criminal.

521
00:20:55.732 --> 00:20:57.038
You said you were past that.

522
00:20:57.081 --> 00:21:00.259
I lied.
We need to find Olek. Taylor.

523
00:21:04.175 --> 00:21:05.960
Oh. who am I kidding?
I hate being on the bench.

524
00:21:06.003 --> 00:21:08.179
I'm in.
He's not at any
of his known locations.

525
00:21:08.223 --> 00:21:11.270
and his cell and credit cards
have gone dark.

526
00:21:11.313 --> 00:21:14.577
Someone connected to Kovalev
must know where Olek is.

527
00:21:14.621 --> 00:21:16.405
Sure. Let's just stroll

528
00:21:16.449 --> 00:21:17.885
on into Kovalev territory
and say.

529
00:21:17.928 --> 00:21:19.930
"Hey. has anybody seen Olek?"

530
00:21:20.757 --> 00:21:24.761
Actually. that's exactly
what we'll do.

531
00:21:39.733 --> 00:21:41.169
Hello.

532
00:21:43.650 --> 00:21:45.521
I'm a private investigator.

533
00:21:45.565 --> 00:21:48.307
I'm looking for
a man named Olek.

534
00:21:51.397 --> 00:21:52.876
Okay.

535
00:22:03.017 --> 00:22:04.366
I'm looking for Olek.

536
00:22:04.410 --> 00:22:05.715
He's a friend of Kovalev's.

537
00:22:07.456 --> 00:22:09.110
No English.

538
00:22:10.851 --> 00:22:12.113
Well. if you see
him. let him know

539
00:22:12.156 --> 00:22:14.289
Alexis Woods is
looking for him.

540
00:22:26.823 --> 00:22:30.131
I knew it was Kovalev
right away.

541
00:22:30.174 --> 00:22:31.567
How's that?

542
00:22:31.611 --> 00:22:33.395
His picture's been hanging up
in the DEA's office

543
00:22:33.439 --> 00:22:35.310
as long as I can remember.

544
00:22:35.354 --> 00:22:38.095
Besides. you don't
forget a face like his.

545
00:22:38.139 --> 00:22:39.314
What do you mean?

546
00:22:39.358 --> 00:22:40.707
He just looks

547
00:22:40.750 --> 00:22:42.622
like a criminal. you know?

548
00:22:42.665 --> 00:22:44.275
And you have
particular experience

549
00:22:44.319 --> 00:22:45.755
knowing what
a criminal looks like?

550
00:22:45.799 --> 00:22:47.366
Oh. yeah.

551
00:22:47.409 --> 00:22:50.934
I've busted dozens of crooks.
They're all the same.

552
00:22:50.978 --> 00:22:54.024
Must be hard.
working around scum like that.

553
00:22:54.068 --> 00:22:55.722
Reilly.

554
00:22:55.765 --> 00:22:57.593
I do what I can for
the good of the country.

555
00:22:57.637 --> 00:23:00.248
That's what really inspired me
to put my life on the line

556
00:23:00.291 --> 00:23:02.119
every day. you know?
That's what inspired you?

557
00:23:02.163 --> 00:23:04.774
Not the cash?
Okay.

558
00:23:04.818 --> 00:23:05.949
Excuse me?
Stealing cash
from the scenes.

559
00:23:05.993 --> 00:23:06.950
Isn't that what really

560
00:23:06.994 --> 00:23:08.082
inspired you every day?

561
00:23:08.125 --> 00:23:09.605
Hey. Agent Scott.

562
00:23:09.649 --> 00:23:12.086
Give us a minute.

563
00:23:12.129 --> 00:23:14.915
In fact.
we're gonna take five.

564
00:23:19.180 --> 00:23:22.096
You do realize Scott's
testifying for us?

565
00:23:22.139 --> 00:23:23.619
I know. I won't
ask those questions

566
00:23:23.663 --> 00:23:25.316
in front of the jury. obviously.

567
00:23:25.360 --> 00:23:28.581
Obviously. because the jury
is gonna sense your contempt.

568
00:23:28.624 --> 00:23:30.104
You need to find a way
to hide it.

569
00:23:30.147 --> 00:23:33.281
I just can't stomach
that Captain America schtick.

570
00:23:33.324 --> 00:23:34.456
The hypocrisy of it all.

571
00:23:34.500 --> 00:23:35.936
Reilly. the world
is not a binary place.

572
00:23:35.979 --> 00:23:38.242
It as a gray and messy place.

573
00:23:38.286 --> 00:23:39.940
A place where Scott. yes.
is a criminal.

574
00:23:39.983 --> 00:23:41.768
but he's also a man
who's done some good.

575
00:23:41.811 --> 00:23:45.772
In theory. I get that.
but when I see his smug face

576
00:23:45.815 --> 00:23:47.208
going on about his love

577
00:23:47.251 --> 00:23:48.688
of his country.
I want to punch him.

578
00:23:48.731 --> 00:23:50.907
Well. if Scott's face
is the problem.

579
00:23:50.951 --> 00:23:52.300
then replace it with another.

580
00:23:52.343 --> 00:23:53.344
What do you mean?

581
00:23:53.388 --> 00:23:55.129
Try this visualization
technique.

582
00:23:55.172 --> 00:23:56.478
When you're
facing Scott.

583
00:23:56.522 --> 00:23:59.263
picture someone
you trust implicitly.

584
00:23:59.307 --> 00:24:00.569
You think that'll work?

585
00:24:00.613 --> 00:24:02.353
It better.

586
00:24:03.224 --> 00:24:04.834
Why did you become

587
00:24:04.878 --> 00:24:07.446
a DEA Agent. Mr. Scott?

588
00:24:07.489 --> 00:24:10.666
I got into this line of work
because of men like Kovalev.

589
00:24:10.710 --> 00:24:13.626
Because you wanted
to clean the streets?

590
00:24:13.669 --> 00:24:15.802
Yes.
And protect Americans?

591
00:24:15.845 --> 00:24:16.933
Yes.

592
00:24:16.977 --> 00:24:18.413
In doing so.

593
00:24:18.457 --> 00:24:21.024
did you ever place
your own life in harm's way?

594
00:24:21.068 --> 00:24:22.548
Every day.

595
00:24:22.591 --> 00:24:25.507
Weren't you. in fact.
injured in the line of duty?

596
00:24:26.552 --> 00:24:28.989
I was shot right here.
in the shoulder.

597
00:24:29.032 --> 00:24:30.817
Despite this harm
and the risk

598
00:24:30.860 --> 00:24:34.516
of being shot. you proudly
went to work every day?

599
00:24:34.560 --> 00:24:36.866
I did.
Why is that?

600
00:24:38.651 --> 00:24:41.871
Because I took an oath
to protect this country.

601
00:24:43.830 --> 00:24:46.180
No further questions.

602
00:24:48.574 --> 00:24:52.752
Well. look at you. Turned
a corrupt cop into a Boy Scout.

603
00:24:55.189 --> 00:24:56.495
We're done here.
You can take him.

604
00:25:02.718 --> 00:25:03.806
It's a bust.

605
00:25:03.850 --> 00:25:05.416
No one's taking the bait.
It'll work.

606
00:25:05.460 --> 00:25:07.506
Once Olek learns someone's
asking about him.

607
00:25:07.549 --> 00:25:08.811
he'll check the fake website.

608
00:25:08.855 --> 00:25:11.379
It's classic curiosity
killed the cat.

609
00:25:11.422 --> 00:25:13.250
My cat's too smart to let
her curiosity kill her.

610
00:25:14.600 --> 00:25:17.646
Well. someone's not that smart.

611
00:25:17.690 --> 00:25:19.692
Someone's
accessing the site?
As we speak.

612
00:25:19.735 --> 00:25:22.521
And that means my malware is
being dumped onto their system.

613
00:25:22.564 --> 00:25:23.783
Okay. what does the malware do?

614
00:25:23.826 --> 00:25:25.611
It gives me access
to the computer

615
00:25:25.654 --> 00:25:29.658
of whoever's visiting the
site. including their webcam.

616
00:25:34.097 --> 00:25:35.359
It's the guy I gave my card to.

617
00:25:35.403 --> 00:25:36.752
Between you and me.

618
00:25:36.796 --> 00:25:38.101
I should have given him
a breath mint.

619
00:25:38.145 --> 00:25:39.929
Olek?

620
00:25:52.420 --> 00:25:54.335
Any chance he told Olek
to check out our site?

621
00:25:54.378 --> 00:25:56.032
No idea.
But I don't need him to.

622
00:25:56.076 --> 00:25:58.731
I can mine this guy's computer
and hack his recent call log.

623
00:25:58.774 --> 00:26:00.428
And that'll get you
Olek's number?

624
00:26:00.471 --> 00:26:03.126
He drew us a map
straight to Olek.

625
00:26:04.606 --> 00:26:06.913
That was
an impressive turnaround.

626
00:26:06.956 --> 00:26:09.089
So tell me.

627
00:26:09.132 --> 00:26:12.614
whose face did you picture
instead of Scott?

628
00:26:12.658 --> 00:26:15.748
The only face that's never
let me down. Finch.

629
00:26:17.793 --> 00:26:19.708
Ah. Man's best friend.

630
00:26:19.752 --> 00:26:21.928
In some cases.
man's only friend.

631
00:26:24.974 --> 00:26:27.107
I know it's not easy for you.

632
00:26:27.150 --> 00:26:29.283
Having to turn Scott
into a hero.

633
00:26:29.326 --> 00:26:32.591
It feels strange to say. but it
wasn't as hard as I expected.

634
00:26:32.634 --> 00:26:35.594
Is that what's bothering you?

635
00:26:36.595 --> 00:26:38.335
When a government official
goes corrupt.

636
00:26:38.379 --> 00:26:40.773
it's not usually
one big dramatic move.

637
00:26:40.816 --> 00:26:43.993
It's small steps. Each time
there's a justification

638
00:26:44.037 --> 00:26:45.342
for moving the line.

639
00:26:45.386 --> 00:26:48.607
"I need it."
"I deserve it."

640
00:26:48.650 --> 00:26:50.652
Until they can't see
who they've become.

641
00:26:50.696 --> 00:26:52.480
People rationalize
their behavior

642
00:26:52.523 --> 00:26:54.351
to make it acceptable
to themselves.

643
00:26:54.395 --> 00:26:55.962
I thought I'd never
have to worry about

644
00:26:56.005 --> 00:26:57.572
that kind of slippery slope.

645
00:26:57.616 --> 00:26:59.705
if I never got out onto the
slope in the first place.

646
00:26:59.748 --> 00:27:02.359
And tonight. you stepped
out onto the slope.

647
00:27:02.403 --> 00:27:05.406
I did. and I was fine.

648
00:27:05.449 --> 00:27:07.147
The world didn't crumble.

649
00:27:07.190 --> 00:27:09.366
That kind of terrifies me.

650
00:27:09.410 --> 00:27:12.326
What step will I take next?

651
00:27:13.936 --> 00:27:14.981
We found Olek.

652
00:27:15.024 --> 00:27:15.721
What?

653
00:27:15.764 --> 00:27:16.765
Without the DEA's help.

654
00:27:16.809 --> 00:27:18.288
Well. where is he?

655
00:27:18.332 --> 00:27:19.681
I tracked his burner phone
to this neighborhood.

656
00:27:19.725 --> 00:27:21.161
Ms. Rentzel.
I made it crystal clear

657
00:27:21.204 --> 00:27:22.249
that you were to stay away
from the investigation.

658
00:27:22.292 --> 00:27:23.859
There's no warrant
in place.

659
00:27:23.903 --> 00:27:25.208
Whatever you've captured
is completely inadmissible.

660
00:27:25.252 --> 00:27:27.384
I can't...He's on Scott's street.

661
00:27:27.428 --> 00:27:29.560
He's gonna try
to take Scott out.

662
00:27:29.604 --> 00:27:30.692
Call the marshal.

663
00:27:41.921 --> 00:27:43.313
What happened?

664
00:27:43.357 --> 00:27:45.054
Scott went into the backyard
to have a cigarette.

665
00:27:45.098 --> 00:27:48.536
We heard a shot. ran out.
found Scott on the ground.

666
00:27:48.579 --> 00:27:50.059
He's still breathing. but...

667
00:27:50.886 --> 00:27:53.367
...it looks bad.

668
00:27:53.410 --> 00:27:55.151
Olek got to him.

669
00:28:01.810 --> 00:28:03.812
What's Scott's status?

670
00:28:03.856 --> 00:28:05.553
He's alive.
but in a coma.

671
00:28:05.596 --> 00:28:06.685
Will he recover?

672
00:28:06.728 --> 00:28:07.860
It's too early to tell.

673
00:28:07.903 --> 00:28:09.122
As of now. doctors
are giving him

674
00:28:09.165 --> 00:28:11.211
a five percent
chance to wake up.

675
00:28:16.085 --> 00:28:19.654
Do we know
where Olek is now?

676
00:28:19.698 --> 00:28:22.744
I lost his signal not long
after Scott was shot.

677
00:28:22.788 --> 00:28:25.312
Olek's been hiding for a
while. Wouldn't surprise me

678
00:28:25.355 --> 00:28:27.140
if he routinely changes
burner phones.

679
00:28:27.183 --> 00:28:28.924
What about the gun
found at the scene?

680
00:28:28.968 --> 00:28:30.404
Any connection to Olek?

681
00:28:30.447 --> 00:28:31.622
Ghost gun.

682
00:28:31.666 --> 00:28:34.713
- Untraceable.
- If we can't find Olek.

683
00:28:34.756 --> 00:28:35.888
and Agent Scott's
out of commission.

684
00:28:35.931 --> 00:28:37.367
this prosecution's over.

685
00:28:37.411 --> 00:28:39.413
Kovalev's team
will easily

686
00:28:39.456 --> 00:28:40.588
have this case dismissed.

687
00:28:40.631 --> 00:28:42.851
And he'll have added
another body

688
00:28:42.895 --> 00:28:44.635
to his tally--
this time. on my watch.

689
00:28:44.679 --> 00:28:45.898
He had security.

690
00:28:45.941 --> 00:28:46.942
This isn't on you.

691
00:28:46.986 --> 00:28:48.117
I hate that Kovalev's gonna

692
00:28:48.161 --> 00:28:49.466
get away with this.

693
00:28:54.297 --> 00:28:57.474
He won't get away with it
if we have Scott testify.

694
00:28:57.518 --> 00:28:58.606
How?

695
00:28:58.649 --> 00:29:00.869
We recorded his prep.

696
00:29:00.913 --> 00:29:03.654
Of course. We can use that.

697
00:29:03.698 --> 00:29:05.308
Isn't that hearsay?

698
00:29:05.352 --> 00:29:06.832
Technically. yeah.

699
00:29:06.875 --> 00:29:09.312
But there's an exception
called forfeiture by wrongdoing

700
00:29:09.356 --> 00:29:11.532
that allows you to enter
hearsay into evidence

701
00:29:11.575 --> 00:29:13.099
if it's the other side's fault

702
00:29:13.142 --> 00:29:14.448
that our witness
isn't available.

703
00:29:14.491 --> 00:29:18.234
I'd say a coma qualifies
as unavailable.

704
00:29:19.932 --> 00:29:22.108
What happened to Agent
Scott is a tragedy.

705
00:29:22.151 --> 00:29:23.936
But Mr. Kovalev had
nothing to do with it.

706
00:29:23.979 --> 00:29:25.720
You can't be serious.

707
00:29:25.764 --> 00:29:27.766
The night before Scott
is set to testify

708
00:29:27.809 --> 00:29:29.115
against your client. he's shot?

709
00:29:29.158 --> 00:29:31.378
Who do you think did it?
The Tooth Fairy?

710
00:29:31.421 --> 00:29:33.249
- Dr. Bull.
- Need I remind the court

711
00:29:33.293 --> 00:29:34.337
and Dr. Bull

712
00:29:34.381 --> 00:29:35.469
that Agent Scott

713
00:29:35.512 --> 00:29:36.818
routinely put
notorious criminals away.

714
00:29:36.862 --> 00:29:38.820
Yes. like your client.

715
00:29:38.864 --> 00:29:40.648
And Agent Scott
is an admitted thief.

716
00:29:40.691 --> 00:29:42.824
This is a man
who has many enemies.

717
00:29:42.868 --> 00:29:44.434
Judge. with all
due respect.

718
00:29:44.478 --> 00:29:48.525
the timing of Scott's shooting
can't be a coincidence.

719
00:29:48.569 --> 00:29:51.224
Obviously Kovalev ordered
the hit. and therefore.

720
00:29:51.267 --> 00:29:53.487
under the forfeiture
by wrongdoing rule.

721
00:29:53.530 --> 00:29:55.358
we should be allowed to use
the recorded testimony

722
00:29:55.402 --> 00:29:56.795
of Agent Scott.

723
00:29:56.838 --> 00:29:59.101
Do you have any evidence
of Kovalev's involvement?

724
00:29:59.145 --> 00:30:00.711
Not directly.
but we have reason to believe

725
00:30:00.755 --> 00:30:04.890
that Kovalev's associate Olek
acted under his orders.

726
00:30:04.933 --> 00:30:06.630
I don't know any Olek.

727
00:30:07.544 --> 00:30:08.981
Do you have any evidence
to support

728
00:30:09.024 --> 00:30:11.461
your theory
that this Olek shot Scott?

729
00:30:11.505 --> 00:30:13.899
Nothing admissible right now.
but we're working on it.

730
00:30:13.942 --> 00:30:16.205
I agree the
timing is curious.

731
00:30:16.249 --> 00:30:19.208
But it doesn't matter what you
or even I might suspect.

732
00:30:19.252 --> 00:30:21.080
Without something
to hang my hat on.

733
00:30:21.123 --> 00:30:23.386
I can't find that
Kovalev's responsible

734
00:30:23.430 --> 00:30:24.866
for making Agent Scott
unavailable.

735
00:30:24.910 --> 00:30:26.563
Judge Nolan.
we'd like to move

736
00:30:26.607 --> 00:30:27.782
for a directed verdict

737
00:30:27.826 --> 00:30:29.218
in favor of
the defendant.

738
00:30:29.262 --> 00:30:30.567
- Now wait a minute.
- If Your Honor

739
00:30:30.611 --> 00:30:33.179
won't let the video
of Agent Scott in.

740
00:30:33.222 --> 00:30:36.399
we would like to bring
Scott himself in to testify.

741
00:30:37.792 --> 00:30:41.100
There's a chance Agent Scott
might be well enough to testify?

742
00:30:41.143 --> 00:30:42.449
Yes. but he needs rest

743
00:30:42.492 --> 00:30:45.669
rest at the moment.
Give us two weeks.

744
00:30:45.713 --> 00:30:49.586
Mr. Reilly. two weeks
sound right to you?

745
00:30:49.630 --> 00:30:51.719
Yes. Yes. it does.

746
00:30:51.762 --> 00:30:54.678
We just lied to a judge.
A federal judge. at that.

747
00:30:54.722 --> 00:30:56.115
Okay...I could be censured.

748
00:30:56.158 --> 00:30:58.726
We didn't lie. We left things
open to interpretation.

749
00:30:58.769 --> 00:31:00.032
Come on.

750
00:31:00.075 --> 00:31:02.121
Look. Judge Nolan asked
if there was a chance

751
00:31:02.164 --> 00:31:04.210
Scott would be
able to testify.

752
00:31:04.253 --> 00:31:05.776
and I answered truthfully.

753
00:31:05.820 --> 00:31:07.604
Yes. there's a chance.

754
00:31:07.648 --> 00:31:08.910
A five percent chance.

755
00:31:08.954 --> 00:31:10.346
He didn't ask
if it was a good chance.

756
00:31:11.260 --> 00:31:12.914
I guess you weren't
technically lying

757
00:31:12.958 --> 00:31:15.743
to the judge when you
said Scott needed rest.

758
00:31:15.786 --> 00:31:18.180
No. I wasn't.
Okay.

759
00:31:18.224 --> 00:31:20.530
We bought time. For what?

760
00:31:21.967 --> 00:31:24.404
Well. we need to find
evidence that Kovalev

761
00:31:24.447 --> 00:31:26.580
ordered a hit on Scott.

762
00:31:26.623 --> 00:31:29.148
What about that burner phone
that Taylor captured?

763
00:31:29.191 --> 00:31:33.108
Maybe we can use that to get
Olek to flip on Kovalev?

764
00:31:33.152 --> 00:31:35.067
The burner evidence
is inadmissible.

765
00:31:35.110 --> 00:31:36.329
Olek won't
know that.

766
00:31:36.372 --> 00:31:38.026
And once he flips.
it won't matter.

767
00:31:38.070 --> 00:31:40.246
He becomes our evidence.

768
00:31:41.377 --> 00:31:42.596
Okay.

769
00:31:42.639 --> 00:31:44.728
How do we flip Olek
if we can't find him?

770
00:31:44.772 --> 00:31:47.949
Well. I know someone
who happens to be very good

771
00:31:47.993 --> 00:31:50.343
at finding an Olek
in a haystack.

772
00:31:51.213 --> 00:31:53.563
But you might have to do
a little bit of groveling first.

773
00:31:58.003 --> 00:31:59.787
Ms. Rentzel?

774
00:31:59.830 --> 00:32:01.397
I owe you an apology.

775
00:32:01.441 --> 00:32:04.096
I should've included you in the
investigation from the outset.

776
00:32:04.139 --> 00:32:05.706
It's fine. I get it.

777
00:32:05.749 --> 00:32:07.969
You were just doing what you
thought was best for the case.

778
00:32:08.013 --> 00:32:10.972
Any new leads on
Olek's current location?

779
00:32:11.016 --> 00:32:14.280
Not yet. But I recorded
this man's call to Olek.

780
00:32:14.323 --> 00:32:16.108
It's how I found
his burner phone.

781
00:32:16.151 --> 00:32:17.109
I just finished running
their conversation

782
00:32:17.152 --> 00:32:18.458
through a translator.

783
00:32:18.501 --> 00:32:20.112
He asks Olek

784
00:32:20.155 --> 00:32:22.984
if he is still in "the bowels
of the greedy tiger."

785
00:32:23.028 --> 00:32:24.116
The bowels of the greedy tiger?

786
00:32:24.159 --> 00:32:26.727
It might be a Polish expression

787
00:32:26.770 --> 00:32:28.250
for "jeopardy."

788
00:32:28.294 --> 00:32:30.165
Maybe it's not a metaphor.
There is a convenience store

789
00:32:30.209 --> 00:32:33.299
in Kovalev's neighborhood
called The Greedy Tiger.

790
00:32:33.342 --> 00:32:36.128
I wonder if bowels means
he's staying in the basement?

791
00:32:36.171 --> 00:32:38.434
I'll send a team there
right away.

792
00:32:38.478 --> 00:32:40.697
Judge Nolan's
chambers called.

793
00:32:40.741 --> 00:32:42.177
There's a problem.

794
00:32:43.787 --> 00:32:46.007
An affidavit from
Agent Scott's doctor.

795
00:32:46.051 --> 00:32:47.748
Courtesy of Ms. Lamont.

796
00:32:47.791 --> 00:32:51.708
Don't bother. Mr. Reilly.
It's very easy to sum up.

797
00:32:51.752 --> 00:32:53.667
Agent Scott won't
be able to testify

798
00:32:53.710 --> 00:32:55.147
in two weeks
because he's in a coma

799
00:32:55.190 --> 00:32:57.845
with very little chance
of recovery.

800
00:32:57.888 --> 00:32:59.325
So little. in fact. his family

801
00:32:59.368 --> 00:33:00.891
is pulling the plug
this afternoon.

802
00:33:00.935 --> 00:33:02.981
Hmm. Well. then.
Agent Scott's death

803
00:33:03.024 --> 00:33:04.591
will be on your client's hands.

804
00:33:04.634 --> 00:33:07.028
Where is the evidence?
The only evidence I see

805
00:33:07.072 --> 00:33:09.291
is that you and Mr. Reilly
falsely claimed

806
00:33:09.335 --> 00:33:11.032
Scott would be able to testify.

807
00:33:11.076 --> 00:33:12.599
I never said that.
I did not lie.

808
00:33:12.642 --> 00:33:15.036
Enough. Mr. Reilly?

809
00:33:15.080 --> 00:33:16.603
Judge. I'm-I'm sorry
if I misled the court.

810
00:33:16.646 --> 00:33:19.519
but I have an update that
makes this whole issue moot.

811
00:33:19.562 --> 00:33:22.174
We've located Olek.
the man we believe

812
00:33:22.217 --> 00:33:24.089
Kovalev ordered
to shoot Agent Scott.

813
00:33:24.132 --> 00:33:25.699
Well. where is this mystery man?

814
00:33:25.742 --> 00:33:28.223
We only need a few hours
to arrest him and meet with him.

815
00:33:29.268 --> 00:33:31.618
You snowed me for time
once before. Mr. Reilly.

816
00:33:31.661 --> 00:33:32.706
Why should I
believe you now?

817
00:33:32.749 --> 00:33:34.316
This man we're arresting. Olek.

818
00:33:34.360 --> 00:33:36.884
he can testify
as to both Scott's

819
00:33:36.927 --> 00:33:38.625
and Babiack's murders.

820
00:33:38.668 --> 00:33:41.889
But as you stand here now. you
haven't yet arrested this Olek.

821
00:33:41.932 --> 00:33:43.499
So you have no evidence

822
00:33:43.543 --> 00:33:45.806
that Kovalev had anything to do
with Agent Scott's death.

823
00:33:46.850 --> 00:33:47.938
Without Scott. you
have no evidence

824
00:33:47.982 --> 00:33:49.853
that Kovalev murdered BABIACK.

825
00:33:50.767 --> 00:33:52.204
I have no choice

826
00:33:52.247 --> 00:33:55.120
but to grant Ms. Lamont's motion
and dismiss this case.

827
00:33:55.163 --> 00:33:56.251
Let's go to court

828
00:33:56.295 --> 00:33:58.079
and put it on the record.Please.

829
00:33:58.123 --> 00:34:00.473
You can't let Kovalev
get away with this.

830
00:34:00.516 --> 00:34:03.084
I'm sorry. Mr. Reilly.
You've left me no other option.

831
00:34:03.128 --> 00:34:04.564
Don't do this.

832
00:34:04.607 --> 00:34:06.957
Mr. Reilly. please move.

833
00:34:08.263 --> 00:34:10.309
Come on. Let's get
this wrapped up.

834
00:34:16.576 --> 00:34:17.751
What the hell?

835
00:34:17.794 --> 00:34:19.579
Son of a bitch.

836
00:34:19.622 --> 00:34:20.884
That's one way to object.

837
00:34:26.151 --> 00:34:27.456
Your Honor. let's
take a breath.

838
00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:29.458
Let's take a breath?
I just got sucker punched

839
00:34:29.502 --> 00:34:31.112
in my own chambers.

840
00:34:31.156 --> 00:34:32.766
You can forget about
going to court.

841
00:34:32.809 --> 00:34:35.247
I'm gonna sign an order of
dismissal right here. right now.

842
00:34:35.290 --> 00:34:38.119
Clearly. A.U.S.A.
Reilly is having

843
00:34:38.163 --> 00:34:39.903
some sort of mental breakdown.

844
00:34:39.947 --> 00:34:41.992
But please don't
dismiss this case.

845
00:34:42.036 --> 00:34:43.211
Not. at least.
until you've heard

846
00:34:43.255 --> 00:34:44.299
the argument as to
why you shouldn't.

847
00:34:44.343 --> 00:34:45.344
Argument
from what attorney?

848
00:34:45.387 --> 00:34:46.649
I'm not letting this maniac

849
00:34:46.693 --> 00:34:48.042
back into my courtroom.

850
00:34:48.086 --> 00:34:50.436
I can have an attorney here
by the end of the day.

851
00:34:50.479 --> 00:34:52.177
Chester Palmer.
Okay. clearly.

852
00:34:52.220 --> 00:34:53.656
this is just another
stall tactic.

853
00:34:53.700 --> 00:34:56.137
If you dismiss this case now.
Kovalev walks.

854
00:34:56.181 --> 00:34:58.661
Until he is inevitably
brought to trial again.

855
00:34:58.705 --> 00:35:00.185
He just killed
a witness.

856
00:35:00.228 --> 00:35:03.405
Who's next? A juror? A judge?

857
00:35:04.667 --> 00:35:06.887
Have Mr. Palmer here
by the end of the day.

858
00:35:06.930 --> 00:35:09.150
As for you.
Mr. Reilly.

859
00:35:09.194 --> 00:35:11.109
I never want to see
your face in my chambers

860
00:35:11.152 --> 00:35:12.849
or courtroom again.

861
00:35:12.893 --> 00:35:14.460
Understood.
Get him out of here.

862
00:35:14.503 --> 00:35:16.549
He can cool off
in a holding cell.

863
00:35:16.592 --> 00:35:18.116
Yes. Your Honor.

864
00:35:19.726 --> 00:35:21.162
You went full opera.

865
00:35:21.206 --> 00:35:24.557
Make it worth it.
Lock Kovalev up.

866
00:35:33.566 --> 00:35:35.394
Hey. Olek.

867
00:35:38.919 --> 00:35:40.616
Get on the ground.

868
00:35:42.096 --> 00:35:43.924
Hands behind your back.

869
00:35:47.449 --> 00:35:49.234
You have the right
to remain silent.

870
00:35:50.278 --> 00:35:52.672
We can place you
near Agent Scott's street

871
00:35:52.715 --> 00:35:54.587
minutes before he was shot.

872
00:35:55.588 --> 00:35:57.155
Okay.

873
00:35:59.244 --> 00:36:02.421
Look. you're not the one
we want. Olek.

874
00:36:02.464 --> 00:36:06.903
I've been deputized by the DOJ
to offer you a one-time deal:

875
00:36:06.947 --> 00:36:08.688
admit that Kovalev

876
00:36:08.731 --> 00:36:11.734
ordered the hit on
Agent Scott. admit that

877
00:36:11.778 --> 00:36:15.216
it was your gun at the scene.

878
00:36:15.260 --> 00:36:17.827
and you're a free man.

879
00:36:18.915 --> 00:36:20.874
I have nothing to say.

880
00:36:20.917 --> 00:36:23.746
Scott was a federal agent.

881
00:36:23.790 --> 00:36:26.227
That's a capital offense.

882
00:36:26.271 --> 00:36:28.316
That's the death penalty.

883
00:36:28.360 --> 00:36:30.710
Use your head. Olek.

884
00:36:30.753 --> 00:36:32.625
Give Kovalev up.

885
00:36:35.018 --> 00:36:37.282
Are you afraid he's gonna
have you killed. too?

886
00:36:37.325 --> 00:36:39.719
Because we can
offer you protection.

887
00:36:40.589 --> 00:36:42.809
Kovalev would not kill me.

888
00:36:44.158 --> 00:36:46.726
He knows you can bring him down.

889
00:36:48.293 --> 00:36:50.817
Kovalev is not a bad man.

890
00:36:50.860 --> 00:36:52.340
People fear him.

891
00:36:52.384 --> 00:36:56.126
I do not know why.
but they do.

892
00:36:56.170 --> 00:36:58.520
Maybe your friend.

893
00:36:58.564 --> 00:37:02.872
this. um. Agent Scott.

894
00:37:02.916 --> 00:37:07.355
maybe he feared testifying
against Kovalev.

895
00:37:07.399 --> 00:37:11.664
Maybe he feared so much.
he take his own life.

896
00:37:11.707 --> 00:37:14.493
I don't know.
Maybe it was his gun you found.

897
00:37:14.536 --> 00:37:15.972
Maybe he pull trigger.

898
00:37:16.016 --> 00:37:19.106
Okay. I don't have time
for this garbage. man.

899
00:37:19.149 --> 00:37:20.499
Shame. really.

900
00:37:21.630 --> 00:37:25.373
Kovalev never would have
harmed him.

901
00:37:26.287 --> 00:37:28.594
Kovalev would never harm anyone.

902
00:37:30.378 --> 00:37:31.379
Did we get him?

903
00:37:31.423 --> 00:37:32.685
We got Olek.

904
00:37:32.728 --> 00:37:34.556
but he won't flip on Kovalev.

905
00:37:34.600 --> 00:37:36.689
He even had the gall
to say that Agent Scott

906
00:37:36.732 --> 00:37:39.387
was so scared of Kovalev
that he killed himself.

907
00:37:39.431 --> 00:37:40.954
That's absurd.

908
00:37:40.997 --> 00:37:43.304
Yeah.

909
00:37:43.348 --> 00:37:45.567
This forfeiture
by wrongdoing rule.

910
00:37:45.611 --> 00:37:47.395
does it define wrongdoing?

911
00:37:47.439 --> 00:37:48.875
Not in the
rule itself.

912
00:37:48.918 --> 00:37:51.704
It could be harm.
threat of harm. really anything

913
00:37:51.747 --> 00:37:54.750
intended to discourage the
witness from testifying. Why?

914
00:37:55.664 --> 00:37:57.971
Well. maybe Olek has a point.

915
00:37:59.842 --> 00:38:01.888
Maybe Olek does have a point.

916
00:38:03.324 --> 00:38:05.108
What point?

917
00:38:05.152 --> 00:38:07.285
Your Honor. we have uncovered
some last-minute evidence

918
00:38:07.328 --> 00:38:09.548
that we believe...Mr. Palmer. I'm gonna
cut to the chase here.

919
00:38:09.591 --> 00:38:11.767
because I'm a little tired
of the government's games.

920
00:38:11.811 --> 00:38:14.117
Do you have any evidence
of any kind that shows

921
00:38:14.161 --> 00:38:16.294
the defendant tried
to have Scott killed?

922
00:38:16.337 --> 00:38:17.991
No. Your Honor.

923
00:38:18.034 --> 00:38:19.862
Then because there is
no wrongdoing by Mr. Kovalev.

924
00:38:19.906 --> 00:38:22.082
Agent Scott's video testimony
can't come in.

925
00:38:22.125 --> 00:38:25.259
and this case is dismissed
for lack of evidence.

926
00:38:25.303 --> 00:38:26.652
If Your Honor
will indulge me.

927
00:38:26.695 --> 00:38:28.306
that is not
an accurate statement.

928
00:38:28.349 --> 00:38:29.785
We have evidence

929
00:38:29.829 --> 00:38:32.353
that Mr. Kovalev committed
a wrongdoing that made

930
00:38:32.397 --> 00:38:33.572
our witness unavailable.

931
00:38:33.615 --> 00:38:35.095
What wrongdoing?
Your Honor.

932
00:38:35.138 --> 00:38:36.966
we have a statement
from Mr. Kovalev's associate

933
00:38:37.010 --> 00:38:39.795
that Agent Scott shot himself
because he feared Mr. Kovalev.

934
00:38:39.839 --> 00:38:41.884
Now. we believe
Mr. Kovalev's wrongdoing

935
00:38:41.928 --> 00:38:44.496
in this instance is
creating an atmosphere

936
00:38:44.539 --> 00:38:46.585
of paranoia a-and fear.

937
00:38:46.628 --> 00:38:48.238
with the sole purpose

938
00:38:48.282 --> 00:38:51.503
of wrongfully scaring Agent
Scott into harming himself.

939
00:38:51.546 --> 00:38:54.244
Objection. I-I can't
even state a precise basis

940
00:38:54.288 --> 00:38:55.594
for this objection

941
00:38:55.637 --> 00:38:56.986
because I've never heard
such a wild argument

942
00:38:57.030 --> 00:38:58.640
in open court before.

943
00:38:58.684 --> 00:39:01.034
Your Honor. may we approach?

944
00:39:01.077 --> 00:39:02.818
Oh. why the hell not?

945
00:39:11.436 --> 00:39:12.959
Your Honor. you
asked for a showing

946
00:39:13.002 --> 00:39:15.831
of wrongdoing.
something to hang your hat on

947
00:39:15.875 --> 00:39:17.964
in order to enter into
evidence Agent Scott's

948
00:39:18.007 --> 00:39:21.663
truthful and extremely
relevant testimony.

949
00:39:21.707 --> 00:39:25.493
Testimony he would otherwise
have given himself.

950
00:39:25.537 --> 00:39:28.235
if it were not
for the defendant.

951
00:39:28.278 --> 00:39:29.845
But here it is.

952
00:39:29.889 --> 00:39:31.412
A wrongdoing.

953
00:39:33.240 --> 00:39:34.850
Hang your hat.

954
00:39:35.938 --> 00:39:37.810
And after BABIACK and Olek

955
00:39:37.853 --> 00:39:40.508
began to argue.
what happened next?

956
00:39:40.552 --> 00:39:42.467
Kovalev pulled this gun
out of his jacket

957
00:39:42.510 --> 00:39:44.338
and shot BABIACK dead.

958
00:39:44.382 --> 00:39:46.514
He didn't hesitate.

959
00:39:46.558 --> 00:39:49.474
He just shot him.
like it was no big deal.

960
00:39:49.517 --> 00:39:52.433
That is the kind of monster
that Kovalev is.

961
00:39:58.570 --> 00:40:00.528
Has the jury reached a verdict?

962
00:40:00.572 --> 00:40:02.008
We have. Your Honor.

963
00:40:02.051 --> 00:40:05.359
We the jury find the defendant
Danilo Kovalev

964
00:40:05.403 --> 00:40:08.014
guilty on all counts.

965
00:40:11.365 --> 00:40:13.411
You better get
me out of this.

966
00:40:13.454 --> 00:40:15.630
You hear me?

967
00:40:26.162 --> 00:40:28.817
Well. look who's a free man.

968
00:40:28.861 --> 00:40:31.994
Well. not free enough to go
into Judge Nolan's courtroom.

969
00:40:32.038 --> 00:40:33.169
but free nonetheless.

970
00:40:33.213 --> 00:40:34.519
Thank you.

971
00:40:34.562 --> 00:40:36.434
For all you and your team
did for this case.

972
00:40:36.477 --> 00:40:37.957
Because of you.

973
00:40:38.000 --> 00:40:40.394
Kovalev is gonna spend the rest
of his life behind bars.

974
00:40:40.438 --> 00:40:41.526
What about you?

975
00:40:41.569 --> 00:40:42.875
I will probably
be censured.

976
00:40:42.918 --> 00:40:46.574
Definitely kicked
down the career ladder.

977
00:40:46.618 --> 00:40:48.315
Guessing I'll be on
misdemeanor duty for a while.

978
00:40:48.358 --> 00:40:49.882
I'm sorry to hear that.

979
00:40:49.925 --> 00:40:51.100
Don't be sorry.

980
00:40:51.144 --> 00:40:53.494
I should be disciplined.
I punched a judge.

981
00:40:53.538 --> 00:40:54.669
Being disciplined means

982
00:40:54.713 --> 00:40:57.150
the system is working.

983
00:40:57.193 --> 00:40:59.108
Ah.

984
00:40:59.152 --> 00:41:00.283
I admire your outlook

985
00:41:00.327 --> 00:41:02.285
in the face
of demotion.

986
00:41:02.329 --> 00:41:03.939
How about I buy you lunch?

987
00:41:03.983 --> 00:41:05.027
That's a great idea.

988
00:41:05.071 --> 00:41:06.594
Convictions always
make me hungry.

989
00:41:06.638 --> 00:41:08.857
I just have to grab my clock.

990
00:41:08.901 --> 00:41:10.729
Clock?

991
00:41:10.772 --> 00:41:12.644
Hey. did you know
that. uh. casinos

992
00:41:12.687 --> 00:41:14.428
don't have clocks on the floor?

993
00:41:14.472 --> 00:41:15.777
Yes. so the customers

994
00:41:15.821 --> 00:41:18.084
will lose track of time
and keep gambling.

995
00:41:18.127 --> 00:41:20.347
Exactly. And you know.

996
00:41:20.390 --> 00:41:22.088
the longer
jurors deliberate.

997
00:41:22.131 --> 00:41:23.959
the greater the chance
they'll choose to convict?

998
00:41:24.003 --> 00:41:26.135
You removed the
clock so the jurors

999
00:41:26.179 --> 00:41:28.311
wouldn't realize how long
they've been deliberating

1000
00:41:28.355 --> 00:41:30.400
in order to persuade them

1001
00:41:30.444 --> 00:41:31.793
to convict?
Yes.

1002
00:41:31.837 --> 00:41:33.491
Before the jury
came in this morning.

1003
00:41:33.534 --> 00:41:35.362
That's very unorthodox.

1004
00:41:35.405 --> 00:41:37.712
Most good ideas are.

1005
00:41:37.756 --> 00:41:40.323
And so the student
became the master.

1006
00:41:40.367 --> 00:41:42.412
Learning from the best.

